  38,40,And he will indeed have ňĻa status ofňļ closeness to Us and an honourable destination
  38,41,"And remember Our servant Job, when he cried out to his Lord, ‚ÄúSatan has afflicted me with distress and suffering.‚ÄĚ"
  38,42,"ňĻWe responded,ňļ ‚ÄúStomp your foot: ňĻnowňļ here is a cool ňĻand refreshingňļ spring for washing and drinking.‚ÄĚ"
  38,43,"And We gave him back his family, twice as many, as a mercy from Us and a lesson for people of reason"
  38,44,"ňĻAnd We said to him,ňļ ‚ÄúTake in your hand a bundle of grass, and strike ňĻyour wifeňļ with it, and do not break your oath.‚ÄĚ¬†We truly found him patient. What an excellent servant ňĻhe wasňļ! Indeed, he ňĻconstantlyňļ turned ňĻto Allahňļ"
  38,45,"And remember Our servants: Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob‚ÄĒthe men of strength and insight"
